title: For Sale:  AR15 to PS90 Upper PWA AR57 5.7x28 NIB 16 inch Fluted Barrel Quad Rail 1 FN Magazine $650 + $39
location: TN 90 mi East of Memphis, Memphis, Tennessee
postcontent:
We cannot ship this to some jurisdictions; please read the entire ad carefully before bidding or offering to buy. This listing is for ONE upper and ONE magazine. Dealers, collectors, and law enforcement, however, may take any number of extra packages at the same price and with no additional shipping charges. Here is a complete upper that enables owners of AR-15 type rifles to convert their gun into something as good as an FN P-90 rifle, for about 1/3 of the usual cost. This is PW Arms’s AR57 Upper. The receiver and its component rails begin with a single block of Aircraft Grade 7075 T6 aluminum, rated at 83000 PSI strength. The entire upper is precision milled to within .002 tolerance. This upper is well ported for heat dissipation, and comes with an integral picatinny quad-rail system. The assembly process’s final steps include Infused Hard Coat Anodized finish on the alloy, and parkerization on steel surfaces, installation of front and rear sight area picatinny rails. GBQ Parkerizing process ensures finish durability on the steel. Barrel is 16.04 inch 4 channel fluted, free floating with open ended flash suppressor. Rate of twist is 1: 8.5 inches. Bolt is heat treated 4140 chrome alloy parkerized, like the barrel. Receiver and rail block measures just over 17 inches overall length; from the receiver back to the muzzle end, total length is 24 9/16 inches. This upper receiver comes furnished with a 3 5/8 inch Carbine buffer; owners of A2 rifles will need an AR type buffer. The most important feature of this upper, writes the factory, is its reliability. Unlike many other receivers, they continue, there is no gas system to become clogged with carbon or fouling. The chamber stays clean well beyond extended shooting sessions. Simplicity is key, they summarize, with the free sliding bolt being the only moving element. Its easy removal makes maintenance literally a snap. The AR-57 system ejects spent rounds through the lower’s magazine well, another plus. Factory cautions against using non-factory or non-FN magazines; against using reloaded or non-SAAMI approved ammunition. While we have never heard of any of these requiring the receiver to be fitted, that is always a possibility that a buyer needs to be prepared for. While these assemblies do not come furnished with any magazine from the factory, we are including the buyer’s choice of an FN Factory 10 rounder or 50 rounder. postcontent:
The TA31RCO-M150CP is an Advanced Combat Optical Gun sight (ACOG) designed for the US Army's M4 weapon system. It incorporates dual illumination technology using a combination of fiber optics and self- luminous tritium. This allows the aiming point to always be illuminated without the use of batteries. The tritium illuminates the aiming point in total darkness, and the fiber optic self-adjusts reticle brightness during daylight according to ambient light conditions. This allows the operator to keep both eyes open while engaging targets and maintaining maximum situational awareness. Designed to the exact specifications of the United States Army, the unique reticle pattern provides quick target acquisition at close combat ranges while providing enhanced target identification and hit probability out to 800 meters utilizing the Bullet Drop Compensator. No tools are needed for windage and elevation adjustments because the TA31RCO-M150CP features external windage and elevation adjusters, making it waterproof up to 11m without caps.

The TA31RCO-M150CP also includes:

 1 Thumbscrew Flattop Adapter (TA51)

The main module of the P250 is an internal stainless steel frame fire control unit which consist of the integrated fire control group (trigger, hammer and all necessary linkage and springs), ambidextrous slide release (one on each side of the pistol), ejector and four slide rails. This steel receiver unit is used in every P250 grip module, top end, and chambering combination and is inserted into the grip frame module and held in place by the axis pin of the disassembly lever. This course exceeds all firearms safety training requirements of Oregon's concealed handgun law pursuant to ORS 166.291(f)(G). You will receive a certificate of completion which you can submit to your local Sheriff's office with your concealed handgun license application. 

Subjects covered are: Basic Handgun Safety, Tactical Issues, CCW Firearms, Ammunition, Holsters, Gun Free Zones, Reciprocity, Storage, Oregon "Use of deadly force laws" 

After attending this class you will have a fundamental understanding about firearm and handgun safety and the rights and responsibilities associated with the carrying of a concealed Handgun in the State of Oregon. 

This is NOT a live firing class. Do NOT bring a firearm with you to the class. 

Even though the class time is only 90 minutes long, there will be time for questions and answers after the class. 

More Information: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/schedule.php?IDNum=39 
 Download a Flyer: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/ClassFlyer/oregon-concealed-handgun-license-class-5-2-2014.pdf

title: For Sale:  Mosin-Nagant M44 prices
postcontent:
After seeing over-priced M44's get posted repeatedly, here is a public service announcement for those that are interested in this fine firearm.

M44's can be bought in good condition with no cosmoline and full kit (minus sling and pouch) for $170 here: https://www.wideners.com/itemdetail.cfm?item_id=7006

Surplus ammunition can be found for .20 cents per round here: http://www.cheaperthandirt.com/product/AMM-653

Good quality non-corrosive soft point hunting ammo can be found for .79 cents per round here: http://www.selwayarmory.com/prvipartizan762x54r150grsoftpoint-boxof20.aspx

It's a cheap gun that's accurate, powerful, tough as nails and will only go up in value. Everyone who was around when the surplus German Mausers hit the market are now kicking themselves for not buying more. They used to sell for $100-150, now they're $450+.

So don't dither, buy one. You don't have to buy it from the link above, but buy one. Buy 20 if you can.

Protips: Polish the chamber. Get a recoil pad - the full size Mosin kicks hard, this carbine model is lighter and kicks like you wouldn't believe so, seriously, get a pad (Amazon has a custom fit pad for $9 http://www.amazon.com/Mosin-Nagant-Rubber-Recoil-Butt/dp/B001HIT1UO ). Get the proper tool if you need to drift the front sight. Be sure of your backstop, the military round punches right through big trees.

Good luck, have fun, don't get gouged.

location: TN 90 mi East of Memphis, Memphis, Tennessee
postcontent:
Our # XMTISMAT910

NO New York City. This listing is for THREE Magazines. Hit Buy It and you’re buying 3, not 1. Buyers, however, may take any number of extras we have available at the same per-mag price, and with no additional shipping charges. For the past few years, American Tactical Imports has led us to appreciate Turkish Gunmaking Finesse. Here is ATI’s factory 10 shot magazine for its well made, slick-finished FS9, CS9, and HP9 series of pistols, modeled and named after John Moses Browning’s 1935 Hi-Power. Italian influence, rather than Belgian, is more in evidence on the pistol itself as well as on its magazine. The tell-tale marking on the magazine is its patent number 5386657, a Mec-Gar patent. These magazines also fit the ATI FS-9 and CS-9 pistols. Interestingly, it will not fit a 92F series Beretta, but it works just fine in the Beretta 8000 Cougar pistols with only a quarter inch or so of protrusion past the butt of the Cougar’s grip frame, as the photos show. Construction is smooth bright blue finished steel, with steel spring and heavy duty black polymer extended floorplate and cartridge follower. This magazine flush fits the grip frame of the HP-9 pistol, as opposed to its standard issue extended twenty rounder.
